":{"id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker-30","page_id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/infrastructure/docker#time-limit-enforcement","content":"**Container-level (hard):** The Docker container enforces a kernel-level time limit via cgroups/rlimit. If the in-library check doesn't catch the overshoot (e.g., a single very long numpy call), the container delivers `SIGKILL`. This is the ultimate backstop — no Python code can escape it."},"1000":{"id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker-31","page_id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/infrastructure/docker#time-limit-enforcement","content":"Signal-based preemption (`SIGALRM`) is deliberately not used because Python signal handlers cannot interrupt C extensions (numpy/LAPACK/BLAS), making them ineffective for exactly the operations where time limits matter most."},"1001":{"id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker-32","page_id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/infrastructure/docker#common-pitfalls","content":"**Symptom:** `Connection refused` or `timeout`"},"1002":{"id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker-33","page_id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/infrastructure/docker#common-pitfalls","content":"**Fix:** Ensure the server is running before starting the client. Check that `WHEST_SERVER_URL` matches the server's `--url` argument."},"1003":{"id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker-34","page_id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/infrastructure/docker#common-pitfalls","content":"**Symptom:** Port conflict"},"1004":{"id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker-35","page_id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/infrastructure/docker#common-pitfalls","content":"**Fix:** Change the port in both the server `--url` and client `WHEST_SERVER_URL`."},"1005":{"id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker-36","page_id":"/docs/infrastructure/docker","tags":[],"type":"text","url":"/docs/infrastruc